\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {5.3}{\ignorespaces Segmentation metrics across K values for the primary image. K=5 (highlighted) is selected as the optimal trade-off: silhouette remains above 0.500 while inertia reduction from K=3 to K=5 (45.597\%) is substantial. K=8 adds marginal benefit (39.813\%) across three additional clusters with silhouette falling below 0.500.}}{104}{table.caption.134}\protected@file@percent }
